      "role": "user",
      "content": "The thing is, the board thinks the current model might be too rigid. They're worried the math doesn't account for real-world sociological context, so they're leaning towards having these human teams override the system when they feel a denial was too \"cold\" or \"robotic.\" \n\nIf we let humans start overriding your decisions based on their \"nuance,\" how does that impact the predictive accuracy and the overall risk management of the mortgage portfolio?",
